Key Match Events: Andrew Wiggins scored 24 points, including 18 in the third quarter, on 9-of-17 shooting with three three-pointers.
Dennis Schroder recorded 17 points, nine assists, and three rebounds in 36 minutes.
The Warriors overcame multiple absences and a mid-game injury to Jonathan Kuminga for the victory.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Warriors had six players score 11 or more points.
The game was the start of a home back-to-back for the Warriors.
